definitions.definition: The feeling of annoyance at impossibility from resistance or inability to achieve something.
The act of frustrating , or the state, or an instance of being frustrated .

subdefinitions.definition: The state of contract that allows a party to back away from its contractual obligations due to ( unforeseen ) radical changes to the nature of the thing a party has been obligated to.

definitions.definition: Anger not directed at anything or anyone in particular.
